const findStart = !(100 - 1 in lookup); // true (100 is start)`,conceptContext:"To identify sequence streaks in linear time, save elements into an object lookup index. Then, query only element starts to bypass duplicate checks.",description:"To complete the Object Dictionaries sequence, let's solve a high-speed streak validation test.\n\nWrite a function `longestStreak(nums)` that takes an array of unsorted integers and identifies the length of its longest consecutive sequence of numbers.\n\nExample: `[100, 4, 30, 1, 3, 2]` contains consecutive sequence `1, 2, 3, 4`, returning a length of `4`.\n\nAchieve O(N) complexity using helper hash maps.",codeTemplate:`function longestStreak(nums) {
